	ctaContact: "หรือถ้าอยากคุยกัน เขียนหาเราที่ hello@paritsea.co",
} : {
	title: "About Paritsea",
	eyebrow: "Behind the Way of Thinking",
	heroHeadline: "A way of thinking that understands both\nthe complexity of the world\nand the depth of people — born from life",
	heroBody: "Paritsea is a way of thinking that reads people and systems together.\nBorn from real experience across business, organizations, and human relationships.\nNot abstract. A method that surfaces hidden structures, human costs, and the tension between them — without losing sight of the people inside.",
	sections: [
		{
			title: "The Question That Started It All",
			content: "Paritsea began with a question that kept surfacing across contexts\n— no matter the industry, the team, or the relationship.\n\nFrom the person carrying an entire organization alone, unseen,\nto the most capable people in a team burning out while the system stayed silent.\n\nFrom organizations with perfect strategies that everyone knew wouldn't work,\nto relationships that fell apart — not because anyone was bad,\nbut because no one understood what was actually happening.\n\nFrom people starting over, afraid of repeating the same patterns,\nto people who succeeded but couldn't understand why they still felt empty.\n\nThe same question, every time:\n\"Why do systems make people responsible for outcomes,\nbut never responsible for the humans inside them?\"\n\nParitsea is the attempt to answer this.\nNot with a new theory.\nWith a language that lets what's invisible — finally be named.",
		},
		{
			title: "Life, Work, Relationships, and Growth Were Never Separate",
			content: "The most unexpected thing about building Paritsea was discovering that\nproblems in life, work, relationships, and growth share the same underlying structure.\n\nA leader who trusts no one to decide for them.\nA partner afraid to be vulnerable because they've been hurt before.\nSomeone starting over, afraid of repeating the same pattern.\nA system designed to depend on a single person.\nThese are the same phenomenon. Just in different domains.\n\nOnce you see this,\nseparating 'work' from 'life'\nor 'systems' from 'people'\nbecomes impossible.\n\nParitsea doesn't just connect these dimensions.\nIt reveals that they were connected all along.\nWe just never saw it.",
		},
		{
			title: "The Person Who Saw This Before Anyone Else",
			content: "Paritsea was born from one person — Parit Ritchai.\nNot a collective. Not a community project.\nA system of thinking that emerged from someone who spent years\nobserving, questioning, and connecting what most people overlook.\n\nHe doesn't see himself as a guru or a thought leader.\nHe sees himself as someone who gives names to what people feel but can't say.\n\nWhy do the most capable people burn out?\nWhy do well-run organizations still feel wrong from the inside?\nWhy do good relationships still carry something missing?\n\nThese questions didn't come from a classroom.\nThey came from meeting rooms, from real conversations, from relationships\nwhere he saw that 'systems' and 'people' were never separate —\nwe just never had clear language to say it directly.\n\nParitsea is that language.\nBuilt so that what was invisible can finally be named —\nand what is named can finally be addressed.",
		},
		{
			title: "What Paritsea Does for You",
			content: "Paritsea is open to everyone —\nbecause the strongest way of thinking is one tested in the open.\n\nYou don't need to be a CEO, a psychologist, or a philosopher to use Paritsea. You only need the willingness to look at what most people overlook, the courage to question what's been normalized, and space to observe without rushing to judge.\n\nWherever you are in your life, Paritsea is open for you to read, understand, and adapt — in your own way.",
		},
	],
	ctaDoctrine: "Start with the Doctrine",
	ctaMethod: "Or start with the entry that resonates most",
	ctaContact: "Or write to us at hello@paritsea.co",
};

